Dr. Jill Biden, USAID Administrator Rajiv Shah, and U.S. Ambassador Catherine Russell will be traveling to Zambia, the Democratic Republic of Congo, and Sierra Leone from June 30 to July 7, 2014. The purpose of their travel is to highlight the importance of girls' education and women's participation in various sectors for economic development, improved health and education, democratic governance, and peace and security. These themes will also be discussed during the upcoming U.S.-Africa Leaders Summit in Washington, D.C. in August. More details about the trip will be provided later.